<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-19T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="690" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d690">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5131/473: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-19T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 19,
                                        1927—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>83. Commercial attaché has reported assurances received concerning
                            position of American commerce under proposed new French tariff. He also
                            inquires regarding possible release of statement.</p>
                        <p>The question of commercial relations with France and possible
                            negotiations is of considerable importance and the Department desires
                            report from you and recommendations concerning this matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>